The 2008 Bank Austria-TennisTrophy was a tennis tournament played on indoor hard courts. It was the 34th edition of the event known that year as the Bank Austria-TennisTrophy, and was part of the International Series Gold of the 2008 ATP Tour. It took place at the Wiener Stadthalle in Vienna, Austria, from October 6 through October 12, 2008.
The singles featured ATP No. 10, Rome Masters and Doha finalist, Beijing Olympics doubles gold medalist Stanislas Wawrinka, Beijing Olympics silver medalist, Vi&lt;U+00F1&gt;a del Mar and Munich winner Fernando Gonz&lt;U+00E1&gt;lez, and Stuttgart, Kitzb&lt;U+00FC&gt;hel, Los Angeles, Washington champion, Tokyo finalist Juan Mart&lt;U+00ED&gt;n del Potro. Also present were Nottingham winner Ivo Karlovi&lt;U+0107&gt;, Umag titlist Fernando Verdasco, Tommy Robredo, Gilles Simon and Ga&lt;U+00EB&gt;l Monfils.
Champions
Singles
Philipp Petzschner def.  Ga&lt;U+00EB&gt;l Monfils, 6&lt;U+2013&gt;4, 6&lt;U+2013&gt;4
It was Philipp Petzschner's 1st career title.
